{
  "texts": [
    "Given the great heterogeneity of monitoring targets and tools described in previous sections, we envision three key challenges to consider in making surveillance systems effective at large scales and fit to different purposes.",
    "The first challenge is institutional and economic (Meynard et al. 2020).",
    "Data gathering, sharing and early analysis are key to the success of early detection of outbreaks or shifts in ecosystem health.",
    "Transboundary practices and policies can hinder monitoring and management, which need to cover national and transnational strategies, sometimes spanning distinct governmental and non-governmental organizations.",
    "The political will and associated funding are fundamental in this context, given our global economies."
  ]
}